60 mage here... I have a hard time soloing the greenies on the ground floor (I have all my spells except epic).  My 57 earth/59 air can't solo even one spider, so I need to nuke a couple times.  I can pull about 2 or 3 spiders before both my pet and I need to rest for like 5-8 minutes.<br>
<br>
And in 2 hours, about 15-20 spiders, not a single thread dropped.  Got one gem (flawed topaz I think), a couple silks, a couple stackable and non-stackable velium, and that's it.<br>
<br>
This is just insane.  And I can't get anyone 55+ to help me (I don't really know anyone below 50) since they don't get any experience here.  And getting someone who also needs threads makes this pointless since they are such an insanely rare drop. <p>AbMagFab baFgaMbA<BR>
60th High Elf Arch Mage<BR>
Master: Baker(135) Potter(148) Tailor(120) Smith(102) Brewer(188) Fletcher(155) Drinker(171)<BR>Aspiring: Jeweler(1)<BR>
25 of 28 epic pieces obtained<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzacatac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#333333>(6/18/01 4:45:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=244.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible to solo in Velketor's Lab?</span><hr size=1> At 54 I've been soloing in there, just keep the pet back away from the mobs and nuke once to pull to pet.  If pet runs out, you will have a train.<br>
I'm not sure if at 51 you can solo-pull them as I can though, so be careful.<br>
<br>
I use 51 earth pet, B3, DS.  All spiders are green but the Crystalline devos give me exp still.<br>
6 hours and I have 35 threads and 4 quest gems (3 melee, 1 for me).  Sold the 3 melee gems, so made some money while doing the quest.<br>
<br>
You will not find any spells, at least I haven't.<br>
<br>
A good place to go at 51 is Cobalt Scar and do the wyverns.  You can also get quest gems there.  Easier to pull and get xp.  But it won't help you with the shawl quest. . .<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.  Try to find a partner if you can, gets boring meditating all the time.  And you have to nuke at least once per spider, plus buff the pet, so it does drain quickly.<br>
<br>
 <p>Zacatac Soulwanderer<br>
High Elf Mage of Bristlebane<br>
Master of Brewing(170), Baking(143), Tailoring(143)<br>Smithing(179), Fishing(170), and Pottery(146)<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucrowleywayfinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crowley Wayfinder</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(6/18/01 5:07:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=244.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lcdmultimedia.com/crowley.jpg W=104 H=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible to solo in Velketor's Lab?</span><hr size=1> I spent 6 hours in Velks on Saturday and was able to get all 75 threads I needed for the shawl. By far the best spot to camp is WAY WAY WAY up top on the highest shelf (its an oval with spawns all around it). It has the highest concentration of crystalline spiders (the only ones that drop the threads), and with a little use of the external camera, I was able to solo pull any other crystalline spiders I saw on the 4 floors below me.<br>
<br>
I spent alot of time swapping in and out pets to get the best combo I could. I found that the best pet to use was the 60 water pet. I pulled every spider with elemental maestrom (low aggro) and just sicked the pet on em. Pet was masked, B4'd, and cadeau'd. Pet would take a huge beat down, but the water pets regen got him up and running in no time (/pet sit down works wonders with water pets). This left me with plenty of emergency mana.<br>
<br>
Also you have to be careful with what spiders you pull. And be prepared to assist your pet on tougher ones. Watchers are the easiest and the pet usually only got down to half when fighting a watcher. Devourers were much harder, usually getting very close to killing the pet, but also had a MUCH HIGHER thread drop rate. And in the 6 hrs I camped I saw 2 Hunters spawn. Crystalline Hunters are DEADLY. I was able to kill both, but I had to unload all my mana and jump off my perch both times to avoid getting eaten as my pet finished him off.<br>
<br>
Another suggestion, get a lvl 40+ druid to go with you (there are only about 4 million of them on at any given time /sarcasm off). At level 40 a druid will get huge exp in a 6 hour camp (yes, with a lvl 60 mage) and can provide extra AC buffs, regen (for the pet) and DOTs. My wife brought her twink druid to help me out for a while just to speed things up and she got 2 yellow bubs (in a hell level) in no time.<br>
<br>
Peace.<br>
