</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 476<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/01 4:49:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=244.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/kschuler/eqmisc/NefPic155x128.jpg WIDTH=155 HEIGHT=128></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible to solo in Velketor's Lab?</span><hr size=1> The ledge Crowley mentioned is where my wife and I do all our thread farming. There are no spiders down the entire length of a really long bridge, and we just fear kite there. The great thing is that once you've pulled all the spiders on the top platform, it's easy to peek over the side and pull them from as far down as you'd like. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz, "Gnome of Action"</b><br>Devout Agnostic Magician of the 56th Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureahkitsunearcanis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reah Kitsune Arcanis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/01 2:18:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=244.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible to solo in Velketor's Lab?</span><hr size=1> Greetings,<br>
<br>
51 Mage here and I've been soloing part of Velks off and on  since hitting 50.  I've found that for me the entrance area with some of the spiders around it are workable but at 51 you cannot solo pull any of the spiders that are grouped.  I've found that I can break the spawns by the right of the door by buffing up a 56 hitter MS2 pet (or 49 Water pet for that matter - gauge the pet against the gargoyles just inside the entrance to see if it's a keeper) and launching the pet into the pair on the right.  Assist the pet and nuke down his first playmate quickly and from range and then give the second one some time.  Once the second one is dead, your pet will/should be at no less than 30% life and then you can med up a bit to recover.  The spiders all seem to be on a 30 minute respawn timer so after the pair on the right respawn you can pull the first before the partner shows and allow some time to stagger them.  Off to the left there is a single spider partially hidden by the ramp, you cannot target him to pull him out safely but you can launch your pet at him and then use SoS to nuke the spider some.  Depending on traffic in there.  Usually it's dead, you can also pick up another single spider or pair from a bit left of the entrance as well.  With the zone to your back it's not usually bad.  Just really boring and no coinage at all.<br>
<br>
Reah Kitsune'Arcanis<br>
